\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {Eddie moved cautiously through the ruins, his footsteps echoing in the vast emptiness. The shattered remains of Craemonia Bastion stretched before him\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 toppled columns, cracked stone archways, and walls worn down by time and nature. The air was thick with dust, the scent of damp stone mingling with the crisp night breeze.}
\par\plain {His eyes scanned the remnants of what must have once been a grand stronghold, now reduced to a skeletal shadow of its former self. What was this place? A fortress? A sanctuary? Or perhaps something more?}
